<HEADLINE> Nawaz Sharif Sentenced to 14 Years' Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Accountability Court of
Pakistan sentenced deposed Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif on Saturday
to 14 years' imprisonment on a charge of tax evasion and
disqualified him from holding any public office for 21 years.
</P>
<P>
Sharif, who is already serving two concurrent life terms on
charge of hijacking and terrorism, also was fined 20 million
rupees (37,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Nawaz Sharif was convicted of buying a Russian-made helicopter
in mid 1990s without showing the price and evading taxes. 
</P>
